// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`ReaderGuidePage > snapshots the full reader guide page 1`] = `"<header data-authed="false">Public header</header><main class="public-container public-methodology-page" id="reader-guide-main"><section class="public-section"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--public-muted, #888)"><a href="/about">About</a><span aria-hidden="true"> · </span><span>Reader guide</span></p><h1 class="public-title">How to read Theseus</h1><p class="public-lede">This is a reading map, not a summary. It will not tell you what Theseus concluded — the conclusions are on the surfaces themselves. It tells you the order to read those surfaces in so that, within roughly half an hour, you can say what the firm claims and how you would test it. Seven stops, each one pointing at a page that already exists, each annotated with how long that page takes.</p><div class="public-card public-method-note" role="note" style="margin-top:1.1rem"><p style="margin:0"><strong>Full path:</strong> 36 minutes, all seven stops. <strong>Fast path:</strong> 22 minutes — steps 1, 3, 4, 5, the shortest route to the claim and the test. Pick the depth you want; nothing here gates on reading all of it.</p></div><div style="margin-top:1.25rem"><div data-testid="reader-tour"><button aria-pressed="false" data-testid="reader-tour-start" style="padding:0.55rem 1.1rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.68rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:transparent;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);cursor:pointer" type="button">Tour me</button></div></div></section><ol style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0"><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-what" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 1</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-what">1 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">What Theseus does</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">Theseus is a research firm that publishes its conclusions and, more durably, the discipline that produced them: recorded deliberation is turned into public theses, each one carrying the method that made it and the record that method has earned. Start on the firm&#x27;s own description of itself.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="/about" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">About the firm →</a></li><li><a href="/" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Public homepage →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-commitment" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 2</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-commitment">8 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">The methodological commitment</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">Before any single method, the firm holds a method for judging methods. The Meta-Method is the document that states it: inquiry is only worth publishing when it can be checked, and the firm commits to scoring its own work against that standard. Everything downstream in this guide is that commitment made inspectable.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="https://github.com/mrquintin/mqtheseuswork/blob/main/THE_META_METHOD.md" rel="noreferrer" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none" target="_blank">THE_META_METHOD →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Methodology explorer →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-criteria" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 3</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-criteria">6 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">The five working criteria</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">The Meta-Method resolves into five criteria the firm applies to every method it uses: Progressivity, Severity, Aim-Method Fit, Compressibility, and Domain Sensitivity. The criteria page carries the exact rubric and composite formula — the same one the running scorer uses, checked against code so the page cannot drift from it.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="/methodology/criteria" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Five-criterion rubric →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-empirical" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 4</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-empirical">12 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">The empirical claims the firm has tested</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">The firm has put its headline claim — that logical coherence leaves a geometric signature in embedding space — on a frozen, public benchmark, replicated it across embedding back-ends, and run an ablation against its own method. The benchmark includes results the firm loses on, and the cross-model study reports a negative finding. Read these for what the claims are and how they have actually scored.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="/methodology/benchmark/qh" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Quintin Hypothesis benchmark →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology/benchmark/qh/cross-model" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Cross-model study →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology/contradiction_geometry" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Householder ablation →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-challenge" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 5</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-challenge">3 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">How to challenge the firm</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">A reader who thinks a conclusion is wrong has a published path to say so. The critique hall of fame carries the severity rubric and every accepted challenge; the response form — the &quot;Challenge this conclusion&quot; affordance on any published article — is how a challenge is filed. Severe critiques carry a bounty. This is the part of the firm designed to be attacked.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="/critiques" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Critique hall of fame →</a></li><li><a href="/post" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Articles — the response form lives on each →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-replicate" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 6</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-replicate">5 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">How to replicate</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">The empirical claims are either reproducible or they are not. The replication harness is a one-command path: clone the repo, run a make target, and compare your reproducibility envelope against the firm&#x27;s recorded runs. The page also documents the dataset, the success rubric, and what to do when your numbers differ.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="/methodology/replicate" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Replication harness →</a></li></ul></li><li class="public-card public-method-card" id="step-subscribe" style="padding:1.1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.75rem;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline"><p class="mono public-muted" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0">Step 7</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0" data-testid="reading-time-subscribe">1 min read</p></div><h2 style="margin:0.15rem 0 0">How to subscribe</h2><p style="margin-bottom:0.6rem">If you want to follow the firm&#x27;s output — new theses, revisions, retractions — the subscriber form below sends a digest at the cadence you choose. Double opt-in, one-click unsubscribe, no tracking pixels. This is the last stop on the map; it is optional.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem"><li><a href="#subscribe" style="display:inline-block;font-size:0.78rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;padding:0.4rem 0.7rem;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #ddd);border-radius:2px;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Subscriber form →</a></li></ul></li></ol><section class="public-section" id="subscribe"><h2>Subscribe</h2><p class="public-muted" style="margin-top:0">The last stop on the map. Following the firm is optional and changes nothing about your access — every surface in this guide is public.</p><div data-subscribe-form="true">Follow the firm</div></section><section class="public-section"><h2>What this guide is not</h2><div class="public-card public-method-note" role="note"><p style="margin:0">The guide indexes; it does not replace. It carries no conclusion, no score, and no claim the underlying surfaces do not already make for themselves. If a step&#x27;s summary and the page it points at ever disagree, the page is correct. A printable version of this same map is kept at <code>docs/Reader_Guide.pdf</code> for readers and journalists who want it on paper.</p></div></section></main>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the completion state with an export control 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="complete" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Tour complete</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">You&#x27;ve completed the tour. This changes nothing — no badge, no gate, no access you did not already have. It is only a record, and only if you want one.</p><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-export" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Export tour record</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-restart" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">Restart tour</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 1: what 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 1 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">What Theseus does</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">This is the firm&#x27;s self-description. Read it for the claim Theseus makes about its own work: it sells conclusions, but the reusable object is the method.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="/about" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">About the firm →</a></li><li><a href="/" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Public homepage →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" disabled="" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 2: commitment 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 2 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">The methodological commitment</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">You are looking at the prior commitment the firm made — the standard it agreed to be held to before it had results. The methodology explorer is this document turned into a working surface.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="https://github.com/mrquintin/mqtheseuswork/blob/main/THE_META_METHOD.md" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none" target="_blank">THE_META_METHOD →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Methodology explorer →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 3: criteria 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 3 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">The five working criteria</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">These five criteria are the rubric. Read them as the test the firm runs on itself: each is a question a method must answer, with the scoring thresholds shown.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="/methodology/criteria" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Five-criterion rubric →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 4: empirical 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 4 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">The empirical claims the firm has tested</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">This is the evidence layer. Note that the leaderboard is one the firm can lose on, and that the cross-model and ablation results include negative findings the firm published anyway.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="/methodology/benchmark/qh" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Quintin Hypothesis benchmark →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology/benchmark/qh/cross-model" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Cross-model study →</a></li><li><a href="/methodology/contradiction_geometry" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Householder ablation →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 5: challenge 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 5 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">How to challenge the firm</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">You are looking at the adversarial channel. The severity rubric is published before you file, so the bounty is grounded in something concrete rather than the mood of the firm.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="/critiques" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Critique hall of fame →</a></li><li><a href="/post" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Articles — the response form lives on each →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

exports[`ReaderTourOverlay — a snapshot per step page > snapshots the overlay at stop 6: replicate 1`] = `"<div aria-label="Reading tour" aria-live="polite" data-testid="reader-tour-overlay" data-tour-status="active" role="dialog" style="position:fixed;right:1.25rem;bottom:1.25rem;z-index:200;max-width:min(28rem, calc(100vw - 2.5rem));background:var(--public-bg-soft, #14140f);border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.1rem;box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45)"><div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem"><p class="mono" style="font-size:0.6rem;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);margin:0">Stop 6 of 7</p><button aria-label="Dismiss the reading tour" data-testid="reader-tour-dismiss" style="background:transparent;border:0;color:var(--public-muted, #999);cursor:pointer;font-size:0.7rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0" type="button">Dismiss ✕</button></div><h2 style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.25;margin:0.55rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">How to replicate</h2><p style="font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.55;margin:0.5rem 0 0;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3)">This is the standing offer the firm makes to be checked. The harness skips models you have no API key for rather than failing, so a researcher who has never spoken to the firm can still run it.</p><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0.7rem 0 0;display:grid;gap:0.3rem"><li><a href="/methodology/replicate" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--amber, #d4a017);text-decoration:none">Replication harness →</a></li></ul><div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;margin-top:0.9rem"><button data-testid="reader-tour-prev" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--public-rule, #444);background:transparent;color:var(--public-fg, #e8e1d3);cursor:pointer" type="button">← Previous</button><button data-testid="reader-tour-next" style="padding:0.45rem 0.9rem;font-family:inherit;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase;border:1px solid var(--amber, #d4a017);background:var(--amber, #d4a017);color:#120d08;cursor:pointer" type="button">Next →</button></div></div>"`;

